import data

data("nyc_airbnb")

nyc_airbnb = 
  nyc_airbnb %>% 
  mutate(stars = review_scores_location / 2) %>% 
  rename(
    borough = neighbourhood_group,
    neighborhood = neighbourhood) %>% 
  filter(borough != "Staten Island") %>% 
  select(price, stars, borough, neighborhood, room_type)

fit model

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = stars, y = price, color = borough)) +
  geom_point()
## Warning: Removed 9962 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

lets fit the model

fit = lm(price ~ stars + borough, data = nyc_airbnb)

lets look at result

more explore

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  nest(data = - borough) %>% 
  mutate(
    modes = map(.x = data, ~lm(price ~ stars, data = .x)),
    results = map (modes, broom::tidy)
  ) %>% 
  select(-data, -modes) %>% 
  unnest(results) %>% 
  select(borough, term, estimate) %>% 
  pivot_wider(
    names_from = borough,
    values_from = estimate
  )
## # A tibble: 2 × 5
##   term        Bronx Queens Brooklyn Manhattan
##   <chr>       <dbl>  <dbl>    <dbl>     <dbl>
## 1 (Intercept) 49.9    18.1    -11.3     -34.3
## 2 stars        4.91   15.8     28.0      43.3

nest even more

nyc_airbnb %>% 
  filter(borough == "Manhattan") %>% 
  nest(data = - neighborhood) %>% 
  mutate(
    modes = map(.x = data, ~lm(price ~ stars + room_type, data = .x)),
    results = map (modes, broom::tidy)
  ) %>% 
  select(-data, -modes) %>% 
  unnest(results) %>% 
  filter(str_detect(term, "room_type")) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = neighborhood, y = estimate)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap( ~ term) + 
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 80, hjust = 1))
